reviews.review: Excellent movie. I especially enjoyed how it fixed the damage that was done in Last Jedi.

Such a disappointment. So much could have been done, but despite too much content, nothing is truly resolved. There's no balance in the force, no explanation of how Palpatine survived or who the Knights of Ren were, or Poe's background or even Fin's for that matter. Even though Rey's family history was revealed, it wasn't fleshed out which is kind of how the whole movie went, everything that happened was glossed over very quickly. Rose was insultingly sidelined (ghosted would probably be a better term for what JJ did to her) & the new characters were so short on screen time that they still felt like strangers by the end.  All the way through it felt like a slight attempt to recreate ROTJ but the end made it clear that's exactly what it was, thereby removing the new identity this trilogy had been carving for itself. What was truly unforgivable for me was what JJ did to Kylo at the end, it was needless & pandering to the old fan base whilst ignoring the new.
Epic conclusion to the Skywalker Saga! Well made and some Fan service, Kylo Ren is awesome, easily the best character of the sequels!!
Everything I ever wanted in a Star Wars film. Fan for 34 years.
Disappointing ending to Star Wars Saga. it might be a little better than Last Jedi but is nothing special. more action than substance.

Very entertaining, Rey has great moments, Daisy Ridley is amazing in that role, Finn and Poe are at their best, but Le√Øla is very distracting, you can feel that her scenes were not shot for this movie. Also watching it I had the feeling that they were trying too hard on the nostalgia factor.
But still a great movie.

It was OK, but the story wasn't strong enough to be a finale. Point blank. There were so many loose ends, we DON'T know what Finn wanted to tell Rey when they thought they were going to die, we know Rey is a Palpatine but it would've been good to get a background of her actual parents. Kylo Ren should've survived...him and Rey joining forces would've lend for a stronger conclusion. 

And, since now Kylo is passed on...it would've been MORE POWERFUL that Solo and Ren join Luke and Leia in that last scene force ghost reunion, that would've spoken more of "family". 

This movie gets me to doubt that the producer was solid on her objective to portray not only the issue of finding yourself, but also of the issue of honoring the past movies before. 

It wasn't completely terrible, but not the story line or ending that would hold weight for me. I still think the original trillogy was way better.
Plot hole after plot hole, such a waste and so disappointed

Force awakens and last jedi had a better opening scene. this opening scene was worrisome. all over the place. and too many character at once. it made the dialogue obviously bad. previous supporting characters were insignificant and the new characters had no purpose. JJ Abrams is truly a YES MAN. does anything to make disney safe and happy.
This one jumped immediately into my top 3 Star Wats films of all time between the original and ESB.
